name: Cadera Baseball - Tee
description: The Texas Rangers are a staple of the Dallas-Fort Worth Metroplex. Established in 1961 and originally known as the Washington Senators, they represented our country by wearing our colors of Red, White and Blue. A couple of cities later, the beloved Rangers still represent the same colors with pride, but now represent the Lone Star State. From Nolan Ryan to Pudge Rodriguez, we wanted to honor the great players and the iconic state. As we push for another pennant and another playoff run, support your team and wear Cadera with pride.

name: Hecho En Dallas - Tee
description:
Part 3 of our "Hecho Series" brings to none other than Dallas, Texas aka Big D, Triple D or D-Town!  Culture and Lifestyle is what Cadera is all about.  We all come from different walks of life and are united by one thing…our CITY.  We represent our city no matter what, good or bad and it has made us who we are today.
 
We felt nothing represented Dallas more than the Legendary Dallas football club.  Silver and Blue with the star that is known all around the world.
 
Triple D, Stand up.  Dallas may be called by some Big D, D-Town, DFW or The Metroplex but to us, call it home.

name: La Dama
description: La Dama Puliendo el paso, por toda la calle real. Polishing the path, along the entire royal street Before starting the Dama concept we wanted to ensure that we paid attention to detail and that we represented the Pin Up Style Culture accurately. We didn't want to simply purchase a Pin Up 101 kit. We wanted the right person, the right attitude, the right look. The shoes, the purse, the flower, the dress…everything needed to be accurate. Our goal was for the Pin Up Culture to look at the image and say, ‘they did it right’. Sexy, smart, quick on her feet, and hardworking. We felt these characteristics needed to represent LaDama. The answer, MissVhaven. We at Cadera cannot express how fortunate we were to find a real life Dama in MissVhaven. Not only is she flat out stunning, but her personality is equally just as beautiful. The most amazing part of MissVhaven is that we didn't have to do anything in transforming her into a Pin Up model. The way you see MissVHaven in the image is exactly the way you will see in real life. Userofreality - Photography. It has been a real pleasure and delight working with Bhavin. His work is simply stunning and breath taking. Bhavin was able to capture all of our ideas and concepts in a single shot. His calming factor and his ability to provide direction is what sets him apart from the rest. Cadera Family, we present to you, La Dama. Be Hip, Be Cadera... Model: MissVHaven Photography: User of Reality Design Work: Kidd Swoosh Shirt Info: District Thread DT104 4.3-ounce, 100% ring spun combed cotton; Sizes run big, shrink to fit.

name: El Musico
description: El Músico trompas de hule, ya no me quiere tocar. Christopher George Latore Wallace, aka Biggie Smalls, aka Biggie, aka The Notorious BIG. There are few songs that can capture an audience simply with the first hook or lyric…. Biggie Biggie Biggie can't you see; Sometimes your words just hypnotize me; And I just love your flashy ways; Guess that's why they broke, and you're so paid; How many times have we sung along to that hook in the club? In the car? Right now!? There is no denying Biggie’s influence in the music industry. We at Cadera are proud to showcase and continue his legacy by selecting Christopher Wallace as our El Musico. To all the ladies in the place with style and grace Allow me to lace these lyrical duches in your bushes Who rock grooves and make moves with all the mommies? Be Hip, Be Cadera... Design Work: Kidd Swoosh Shirt Info: District Thread DT104 4.3-ounce, 100% ring spun combed cotton; Sizes run big, shrink to fit.

name: La Muerte
description: As the saying goes, La muerte, tilica y flaca (Death, lank and skinny). Yeah not so much, not under our watch! With a name like Cadera, lank and skinny are two words we never want in our designs. Our first task was to find a model that wasn't afraid to get into character and bring it. With that said, decision was easy, Marie was the unanimous choice. She has the ability to bring a unique sex appeal to her craft, and we at Cadera knew she was the perfect fit for the job. We didn't stop there. Enter Makeup & Beauty by Gracie, a highly talented Make-Up-Artist and Photographer. She embodies the very definition of a hustler, stopping at nothing to get the right look and shot. Carefully incorporating the “dia de los muertos” look and yet allowing Marie’s beauty still shine through was the key to the success of this design. With all of us working together, under the Cadera Family umbrella, we feel like we killed the concept! (pun intended) Be Hip, Be Cadera... Model: Marie Ramos Photography: Gracie Sosa Make Up Artist: Gracie Sosa Design Work: Kidd Swoosh Shirt Info: District Thread DT104 4.3-ounce, 100% ring spun combed cotton; Sizes run big, shrink to fit.

name: El Tambor
description: No te arruges, cuero viejo, que te quiero pa'tambor! When presented with the card, El Tambor, the one thing that kept popping into our minds wasn't the actual image of a drum but the sound it produced. Sounds of bass-beats and breaks took over our imagination and brought back music video scenes of…LL Cool J, Beastie Boys, The Fat Boys, RUN DMC, Fab Five Freddy. The one common variable between them all was the use of the Boombox, aka Ghetto Blaster, aka Jambox! As we kept letting our imaginations run wild, we continued to have movie scene flashbacks. Movies such as Krush Groove, Breakin’, and Disorderlies all carried and made use of the Boombox. It was as if the Boombox carried a life of its own. It had attitude and it became a symbol for the hip-hop culture. It is, and forever will be, a true 80’s iconic image. It’s loud enough for others to hear, it’s bright enough for others to see, and just like the boombox of the 80’s, Cadera’s El Tambor is here to carry its tradition. Be Hip, Be Cadera... Design Work: Kidd Swoosh Shirt Info: District Thread DT104 4.3-ounce, 100% ring spun combed cotton; Sizes run big, shrink to fit.
